  "instructions": [
    "Preheat oven to 400°F (200°C).",
    "Cut 1-inch cubes of Filipino toast and place on a baking sheet.",
    "Bake in the preheated oven for 5 minutes.",
    "While the toast is baking, mix together the ube halaya, butter, and granulated sugar in a bowl.",
    "Once the toast is done, remove it from the oven and let it cool for a minute.",
    "Dip each toasted bread cube into the ube halaya mixture, coating it evenly.",
    "Place the coated toast cubes on a serving plate and top each one with a sprinkle of shredded ube and a pinch of salt.",
    "Serve warm and enjoy!"
